or=#A62A2A>(6/17/02 5:37:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=102.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question for Warriors....</span><hr size=1> All is in agro control ... i'm a SK and i've mostly play with a monk and that was the monk that was tanking ... <br>
<br>
To avoid taking too much agro i was fighing as max melee limits, avoiding using AC debuff (max taunt with those) and only dark when mob was at 50% or less hp.<br>
<br>
With that i never really had some pb and if i wanted to overtaunt i only had to cast 2 spells (shadow vortex - shroud of pain ..both ACdebuff) or HT ... i was sure to get agro in 99% of the case ... <br>
<br>
And if really too much agro ...well FD is usefull to help your MT build his agro up again. <p><br>
<b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=128257">Menaden</a></b><br>
<b><a href="http://firionavie.org/reso/">Resolution</a></b> Firiona Vie</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uxethux.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xethux</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tyrannical ruler of the Galaxy</span><br>  Posts: 102<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/27/02 11:05:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=102.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> aggro</span><hr size=1> As a monk puller, I've learned a good deal about aggro management. Yethuy (my warrior brother) and I often vie for aggro when we are hunting together, much as you and your friend.<br>
<br>
There are two 2-handed weapons which enable Yethuy to pull aggro from me and pretty much keep it. One is a 2-handed piercing  lance he picked up in Dragon Necropolis that has an incredible damage ratio(I forget the name). The other is the throneblade of Ykesha, which has a decent damage ratio, but nothing incredible, and procs Ykesha, nice proc, but once again, not incredible. But for some reason, that weapon pulls and holds aggro like few others.<br>
<br>
Xethux<br>
<br>
Also, I'm sure you do, but don't forget the other little aggro tools, such as disarm and beg. <p>Confrontation is the essence of nature, confrontation is the rythm of life. In nature violence is pure and purposeful, one species against another an an act of survival.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uthavian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>thavian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/28/02 7:56:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=102.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: aggro</span><hr size=1> Beg can also help keeping aggro? i have never heard of that before. <p><center><b>Takash Bladedclaws</b></center><center>48 Warrior of the Vah Shir</center><center><a href="http://www.geocities.com/theindigovoid">Indigo Void</a></center><center>Firiona Vie</center></center><center>Defender & Slave to the Teir’Dal Priestess Braraa Escrire</center>

</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umixxibixiebane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mixxi Bixiebane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 103<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/28/02 9:56:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=102.topic&index=14>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: aggro</span><hr size=1> Begging is a taunt. Many warriors have beg and disarm as part of their taunt hotkey. You cannot beg while attacking, but it is an extra taunt for those times when you are taunting and not attacking (like taunting a mezzed mob prior to attacking). If you beg while attacking, you just get the &quot;you can't do that while you are attacking&quot; kind of message.<br>
<br>
--Mixxi Moondreamer<br>
52 Halfling champion in the service of Brell<br>
Saga<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uthavian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>thavian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 51<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/29/02 4:01:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=102.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: aggro</span><hr size=1> Thanks Mixxi i will try that next time and yep you do get the message can't beg while attacking i was trying it LOL <p><center><b>Takash Bladedclaws</b></center><center>48 Warrior of the Vah Shir</center><center><a href="http://www.geocities.com/theindigovoid">Indigo Void</a></center><center>Firiona Vie</center></center><center>Defender & Slave to the Teir’Dal Priestess Braraa Escrire</center>

</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubippinfv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>bippinfv</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elf-hugger</span><br>  Posts: 547<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/2/02 1:16:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=102.topic&index=16>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: aggro</span><hr size=1> As Jarkell mentioned somewhere, you can use the old rogue trick of making a macro:<br>
/attack off<br>
/beg<br>
/attack on<br>
<br>
We normally put /hide instead of beg, for evading , but I heard Jarkell needs to taunt now that he tanks so he might be using beg <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=95331" target="blank">Bippin Tenderfoot</a><br> Redeemed Rogue of the 48th blade<br>
