</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umixxibixiebane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mixxi Bixiebane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 108<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/2/02 1:59:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=102.topic&index=17>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: aggro</span><hr size=1> You might lose an attack round with that, though, Bipp, and four or so good whacks generates a lot more hate than begging. Common wisdom is that it's not worth stopping your attack to beg. Just have it in there as a tiny bit more taunt when you're not attacking.<br>
<br>
--Mixxi <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umixxibixiebane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mixxi Bixiebane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 109<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/2/02 2:04:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=102.topic&index=18>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: aggro</span><hr size=1> Proximity and placement make some difference, too. Get in their face and you're more likely to get aggro back, in my experience, and it feels much better to throw yourself in front of that frail caster than to tap the bad guy on the back saying, &quot;Excuse me, but I think you dropped your spleen.&quot;<br>
<br>
'Course, that's for saving beleaguered comrades in single groups, not for raids.<br>
<br>
--Mixxi Moondreamer<br>
52 Halfling champion in the service of Brell<br>
Saga <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ujarkellraven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>JarkellRaven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 854<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/3/02 1:40:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=102.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: aggro</span><hr size=1> If you do it fast enough, you can do it without losing an attack round.  We rogues do it naturally anyway, it's just natural, as all you have to do is replace hide with beg.  Though I find hitting for 445 works well as taunt, too.<br>
<br>
